snippet.textDisplay:
For God's sake take risks with the songs. This is unimaginative at its best. I am tired of Coke Studio just mashing up two songs and arranging it play it as if in some concert and whats's up with folk songs addition at the end though not done in this one. This much variation is done by artists themselves in concerts and i don't think Coke Studio should take that route. 
"Ujaalon mein" is one of the best songs from Faraz. Faiza has great vocal range. An opportunity missed. Turn a Ballad into Rock or Rock into Ballad with risk that blow people away. Results will not be great always but it would keep the soul of Coke Studio atleast. 
Some of the best artists Pakistan has ever produced are working on the show and this output is disappointing to say the least. Fans are proud of Pakistani Music Industry and expect a whole lot more. Coke Studio used to be source of envy across the border. Not so much for past few seasons.
